# 📘 REST API Concepts

---

## 🌐 What is a REST API?

REST (Representational State Transfer) is an architectural style used for communication between systems over HTTP.

It allows a frontend (client) to interact with a backend (server).

---

## 🏗️ Client-Server Architecture

- Client → Sends request  
- Server → Processes request  
- Server → Sends response  

Example:  
User clicks "Add Student" → request sent → backend stores data → response returned.

---

## 🔧 HTTP Methods

| Method | Purpose | Example |
|--------|--------|--------|
| GET | Retrieve data | Get all students |
| POST | Create data | Add student |
| PUT | Replace data | Update full record |
| PATCH | Partial update | Update age only |
| DELETE | Remove data | Delete student |

---

## 🔁 PUT vs PATCH

| PUT | PATCH |
|-----|------|
| Full update | Partial update |
| Replaces entire object | Updates specific fields |

---

